The Miyayama subgroup originally had seven mounds, including one four-cornered protruding mound, two {{ill|Zenpokoho Kofun|ja|前方後方墳|1=zenpō-kōhō-fun|qq=draft}}, three square mounds, and one round mound. Tomb 1, a Zenpokoho Kofun, is no longer extant.<ref name=":A" />
