'''Chūsenji Kofun Group''' (仲仙寺古墳群) is a collection of [[Yayoi period]] mound tombs and [[kofun]] located in {{ill|Yasugi|ja|安来市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yasugi|qq=}}, Nishiakaji Town, [[Shimane Prefecture]]. The group includes several {{ill|four-cornered protruding mounds|ja|四隅突出型墳丘墓|1=X-shaped Burial Mound|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/four-cornered protruding mounds|13=User:Immanuelle/X-shaped Burial Mound|qq=}} and forms part of the broader {{ill|Arashima Tomb Group|ja|荒島墳墓群|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Arashima Tomb Group|qq=}}. It was designated as a [[Historic Sites of Japan|national historic site]] on August 12, 1971, with additional designations made on December 23, 1974.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|和書|title=国指定文化財等データベース|url=https://kunishitei.bunka.go.jp/heritage/detail/401/2220|website=kunishitei.bunka.go.jp|accessdate=2021-02-09|publisher=文化庁}}</ref>
